This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it focuses on language models and ASR models. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of deploying RNNs on resource-constrained mobile devices, which falls under the domain of mobile computing and could be categorized under cs.SD (Systems and Control). The paper also introduces a novel model compression approach, which involves dictionary learning and sparsity, which could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image processing, which could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
